text:
e="preserve">Jimmy Kirunda (1950 – 25 May 2020) was a Ugandan international football player and international football manager for the Uganda national football team. He participated in five Africa Cup of Nations. He was manager of the national team between 1989 and 1996.
Kirunda died of a heart attack on 25 May 2020 in Kampala, Uganda at the age of 70.
